The South African Institute of Electrical Engineers (SAIEE) has appointed Leanetse Matutoane CEO, effective April 1. He has been active in the technical, automotive and engineering consulting operations management industries for a significant part of his career. Matutoane’s achievements include winning a Chairperson’s Award for his role in the startup operations of the Hummer H3 with General Motors in 2007. He joined the SAIEE as operations manager in June 2018. His appointment follows shortly after the organisation’s inauguration of a new president, Prince Moyo.